## Summary

| Severity | Count | Pattern |
|---|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | Zero assertions — tests are no-ops |
| 🟠 High | 4 | `IsNotNull` only — asserts existence, not correctness |
| 🟡 Medium | 6+ | Missing edge/error cases |

**Root cause**: Every test follows the same anti-pattern — call the method to touch the coverage line, then either assert nothing or assert `IsNotNull`. This gives the coverage tool what it wants (line execution) while verifying almost nothing. Any regression in price calculation, CSV formatting, search filtering, or deletion logic would sail through these tests undetected.
